                            <comment id="12900" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Thu, 7 Apr 2005 21:20:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for reporting this! I&apos;ve fixed this through a special slash check, and tested that it works on both the Sun VM and JRockit.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12907" author="ceasaro" created="Fri, 8 Apr 2005 02:50:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Nice to hear you&apos;ve fixed the problem. I also fixed my self probably the same way as you did but had to extend the ClassPathXmlApplicationContext.java and the PathMatchingResourcePatternResolver.java classes. I would like know in which springframework release the fix is present. I&apos;m currently using 2.1.8 and hope I can get rid of own extension code. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;thanks Cees van Wieringen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12909" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Fri, 8 Apr 2005 03:36:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s fixed in 1.2 RC2, to be released early next week. (BTW, there&apos;s a &quot;Fix version&quot; field in JIRA that indicates this.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2.1.8 is the Hibernate version that you use, I assume. Your Spring version will probably be either 1.1.5 or 1.2 RC1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12919" author="ceasaro" created="Fri, 8 Apr 2005 07:45:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m sorry you&apos;re right 2.1.8 is the hibernate version. The spring version i&apos;m using is indeed 1.1.5. Thank&apos;s for the information I will wait till next week en to see the 1.2 RC1 version and take a look at changelog and new features.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
